[DhtmlXQ_comment41]And red would not only be up material-wise, red would also have better positioning.||In Summary:||The 56c with 3rd pawn advancement variation versus  the sandwiched horse defense with left elephant variation is a relatively less complex opening. The pace of the game would also be slower and would allow red to control the game better. ||However, statistical analysis would seem to show that red's efficiency is not that desirable (Jim: that is the game ends in a draw easily). ||The key point in this opening is the mobility of the left red chariot. Its speed of development would have profound effects on the entire game.[/DhtmlXQ_comment41]
